<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><style>body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #FFFFFF; color: #333333; margin: 0; padding: 0; } .container { max-width: 600px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 20px; background: #FFFFFF; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); } h1 { color: #F57C00; margin-bottom: 10px; } h2 { color: #1565C0; margin: 10px 0; font-size: 18px; } p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; margin: 8px 0; } ul { margin: 8px 0 8px 20px; } .section { background-color: #E0E0E0; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 6px; margin-top: 10px; } .footer { font-size: 14px; color: #333333; margin-top: 20px; text-align: center; }</style></head><body><div class="container"><h1>Dear {{clientName}},</h1><p>I am excited to report that the Email Service you requested has been successfully implemented and is now fully functional. All bugs and issues in the previous implementation have been resolved.</p><div class="section"><h2>Summary of Work Completed:</h2><ul><li>Initialized NestJS project and set up Email, Template, and Queue entities.</li><li>Integrated SendGrid as the email provider.</li><li>Implemented a template engine allowing dynamic HTML templates with generic parameters.</li><li>Created a reliable email queue with retry logic.</li><li>Added API endpoints for sending transactional emails, newsletters, and templates.</li><li>Implemented unsubscribe management and email delivery tracking.</li><li>Handled bounce and complaint notifications effectively.</li><li>Configured Docker for seamless deployment.</li></ul></div><p>The email you are reading right now was sent using the very Email Service I just built, demonstrating its full capability to process templates dynamically and handle generic data.</p><p>I am confident this service will streamline all communication tasks and provide a solid foundation for future enhancements.</p><p>Best regards,<br>{{yourName}}</p><div class="footer">Quest Email Service</div></div></body></html>